From 6e213c97967bc68963be94f3bf354b4a5eedc619 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alex <alex@AlexdeMac-mini.local>
Date: Sun, 29 Mar 2026 12:30:39 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] feat: add agent performance benchmarking tools

Created performance comparison tools to demonstrate parallel execution benefits:
- test-performance.html: Full benchmark with real agent execution
- test-performance-mock.html: Mock demo for network-restricted environments

Performance Results (based on mock data):
- Sequential execution: 1.47s (sum of all agent times)
- Parallel execution: 0.30s (max of individual agent times)
- Speedup: 4.9x faster with parallel execution
- Time saved: 1.17s (79.6% reduction)
- Efficiency: 70.1% of ideal parallel speedup

Key Features:
- Visual comparison of sequential vs parallel execution
- Real-time performance metrics display
- Individual agent timing breakdown
- Speedup factor and efficiency calculations
- Implementation code examples

Technical Notes:
- AgentOrchestrator already supports parallel execution
- executeAllParallel() uses Promise.all() for concurrent execution
- executeOptimized() supports dependency graphs for complex workflows
- executeBatched() provides controlled concurrency for rate limiting

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
